(42, 5, 12, 42, 17, 16, 16, 'fell on his face', 'Expressions of Humility and Gratitude', 'This connection highlights the act of falling on one''s face before Jesus in both passages, demonstrating humility and reverence. Additionally, both instances involve a plea for healing or thanks, emphasizing the response to Jesus'' power.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 12, 40, 9, 28, 28, 'thou canst make me clean', 'Faith in Jesus'' Healing Power', 'This connection highlights the theme of faith in Jesus'' ability to heal. Both passages feature individuals seeking healing and expressing belief in Jesus'' power to restore them.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 12, 41, 1, 40, 45, 'if thou wilt, thou canst make me clean', 'Healing of the Leper', 'Both passages emphasize the leper''s plea to Jesus, stating, ''if thou wilt, thou canst make me clean.'' This connection highlights the act of seeking healing and Jesus'' compassionate response to the leper''s condition.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 12, 1, 18, 14, 14, 'thou canst make me clean', 'Divine Power to Heal', 'Both passages emphasize the capability of the Lord to perform the seemingly impossible. In Luke, the leper acknowledges Jesus'' power to cleanse, while in Genesis, God''s promise to Sarah highlights His ability to fulfill His word.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 12, 19, 91, 15, 15, NULL, 'Healing and Divine Presence', 'This connection highlights the theme of calling upon God for healing and deliverance. In Luke, the leper seeks Jesus'' help, while in Psalms, God promises to answer and deliver those who call upon Him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 13, 40, 9, 29, 30, NULL, 'Healing Touch of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the act of Jesus touching individuals to bring about healing. In Luke, he touches a leper, while in Matthew, he touches the eyes of the blind, demonstrating his power to restore health and sight.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 13, 43, 4, 50, 53, 'I will: be thou clean', 'Healing by Jesus'' Word', 'Both passages emphasize the power of Jesus'' words in healing. In Luke, Jesus says, ''I will: be thou clean,'' while in John, He tells the father, ''Thy son liveth,'' leading to immediate healing.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 13, 12, 5, 14, 14, 'be thou clean', 'Healing and Cleansing Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of miraculous healing. In Luke, Jesus touches a leper and declares him clean, while in 2 Kings, Naaman''s obedience leads to his cleansing after dipping in the Jordan.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 13, 26, 36, 29, 29, 'be thou clean', 'Healing and Cleansing Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of cleansing from uncleanness. Both passages emphasize the act of being made clean, with Luke 5:13 focusing on physical healing and Ezekiel 36:29 addressing spiritual and communal uncleanness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 13, 28, 14, 4, 4, NULL, 'Healing and Restoration Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing and restoration present in both passages. In Luke 5:13, the act of healing is immediate, while Hosea 14:4 speaks of healing backsliding, indicating a restoration of relationship.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 13, 1, 1, 9, 9, 'I will: be thou clean', 'Creation and Healing Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine authority in both passages. In Luke 5:13, the act of Jesus saying ''I will'' demonstrates his power to cleanse, paralleling God''s command in Genesis 1:9 to bring forth dry land from the waters, showcasing the transformative power of divine speech.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 13, 19, 33, 9, 9, 'I will: be thou clean', 'Divine Command and Healing', 'This connection highlights the power of divine speech in both passages. In Luke, Jesus commands healing with a touch, while in Psalms, God''s spoken word brings creation into existence.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 14, 3, 14, 2, 32, 'shew thyself to the priest', 'Cleansing of the Leper', 'Both passages emphasize the process of cleansing a leper and the role of the priest in this ritual. Luke 5:14 directly references the command to show oneself to the priest, which aligns with the detailed instructions in Leviticus 14 regarding the cleansing ceremony.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 14, 42, 17, 14, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Cleansing Instructions', 'Both passages emphasize the instruction to ''shew yourselves unto the priests'' as part of the process of cleansing. This connection highlights the continuity in Jesus'' healing ministry and adherence to Mosaic law.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 14, 3, 13, 2, 2, 'shew thyself to the priest', 'Connection of Cleansing Rituals', 'This connection highlights the requirement for a priest''s examination and the offering for cleansing as outlined in both passages. Luke 5:14 refers to the command to show oneself to the priest, which parallels the instructions given in Leviticus 13:2 regarding leprosy.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 14, 40, 8, 4, 4, 'shew thyself to the priest', 'Connection of Healing Instructions', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus instructing the healed individual to show themselves to the priest and offer a gift as commanded by Moses. This connection highlights the continuity of Jewish law in the context of Jesus'' healing ministry.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 14, 40, 12, 16, 16, NULL, 'Instructions to Keep Silent', 'Both passages emphasize the directive to keep Jesus'' identity and actions concealed. In Luke, Jesus instructs the healed man not to tell anyone, while in Matthew, he charges them not to make him known.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
